46 } \
47 } while (0)

53static bool LayoutHasKeyboard(AudioProcessing::ChannelLayout layout) {
54 switch (layout) {
55 case AudioProcessing::kMono:
56 case AudioProcessing::kStereo:
57 return false;
58 case AudioProcessing::kMonoAndKeyboard:
59 case AudioProcessing::kStereoAndKeyboard:
60 return true;
61 }
62
63 RTC_NOTREACHED();
64 return false;
65}

67bool SampleRateSupportsMultiBand(int sample_rate_hz) {
68 return sample_rate_hz == AudioProcessing::kSampleRate32kHz ||
69 sample_rate_hz == AudioProcessing::kSampleRate48kHz;
70}

72// Checks whether the high-pass filter should be done in the full-band.
73bool EnforceSplitBandHpf() {
74 return field_trial::IsEnabled("WebRTC-FullBandHpfKillSwitch");

77// Checks whether AEC3 should be allowed to decide what the default
78// configuration should be based on the render and capture channel configuration

81 return !field_trial::IsEnabled(

85// Identify the native processing rate that best handles a sample rate.
86int SuitableProcessRate(int minimum_rate,
87 int max_splitting_rate,
88 bool band_splitting_required) {
89 const int uppermost_native_rate =
90 band_splitting_required ? max_splitting_rate : 48000;
91 for (auto rate : {16000, 32000, 48000}) {
92 if (rate >= uppermost_native_rate) {
93 return uppermost_native_rate;
94 }
95 if (rate >= minimum_rate) {
96 return rate;
97 }
98 }
99 RTC_NOTREACHED();
100 return uppermost_native_rate;
101}

103GainControl::Mode Agc1ConfigModeToInterfaceMode(
104 AudioProcessing::Config::GainController1::Mode mode) {
105 using Agc1Config = AudioProcessing::Config::GainController1;
106 switch (mode) {
107 case Agc1Config::kAdaptiveAnalog:
108 return GainControl::kAdaptiveAnalog;
109 case Agc1Config::kAdaptiveDigital:
110 return GainControl::kAdaptiveDigital;
111 case Agc1Config::kFixedDigital:
112 return GainControl::kFixedDigital;
113 }
114 RTC_CHECK_NOTREACHED();
115}

144bool AudioProcessingImpl::SubmoduleStates::Update(
145 bool high_pass_filter_enabled,
146 bool mobile_echo_controller_enabled,
147 bool residual_echo_detector_enabled,
148 bool noise_suppressor_enabled,
149 bool adaptive_gain_controller_enabled,
150 bool gain_controller2_enabled,
151 bool gain_adjustment_enabled,
152 bool echo_controller_enabled,
153 bool voice_detector_enabled,
154 bool transient_suppressor_enabled) {
155 bool changed = false;
156 changed |= (high_pass_filter_enabled != high_pass_filter_enabled_);
157 changed |=
158 (mobile_echo_controller_enabled != mobile_echo_controller_enabled_);
159 changed |=
160 (residual_echo_detector_enabled != residual_echo_detector_enabled_);
161 changed |= (noise_suppressor_enabled != noise_suppressor_enabled_);
162 changed |=
163 (adaptive_gain_controller_enabled != adaptive_gain_controller_enabled_);
164 changed |= (gain_controller2_enabled != gain_controller2_enabled_);
165 changed |= (gain_adjustment_enabled != gain_adjustment_enabled_);
166 changed |= (echo_controller_enabled != echo_controller_enabled_);
167 changed |= (voice_detector_enabled != voice_detector_enabled_);
168 changed |= (transient_suppressor_enabled != transient_suppressor_enabled_);
169 if (changed) {
170 high_pass_filter_enabled_ = high_pass_filter_enabled;
171 mobile_echo_controller_enabled_ = mobile_echo_controller_enabled;
172 residual_echo_detector_enabled_ = residual_echo_detector_enabled;
173 noise_suppressor_enabled_ = noise_suppressor_enabled;
174 adaptive_gain_controller_enabled_ = adaptive_gain_controller_enabled;
175 gain_controller2_enabled_ = gain_controller2_enabled;
176 gain_adjustment_enabled_ = gain_adjustment_enabled;
177 echo_controller_enabled_ = echo_controller_enabled;
178 voice_detector_enabled_ = voice_detector_enabled;
179 transient_suppressor_enabled_ = transient_suppressor_enabled;
180 }
181
182 changed |= first_update_;
183 first_update_ = false;
184 return changed;
185}

187bool AudioProcessingImpl::SubmoduleStates::CaptureMultiBandSubModulesActive()
188 const {
189 return CaptureMultiBandProcessingPresent() || voice_detector_enabled_;

192bool AudioProcessingImpl::SubmoduleStates::CaptureMultiBandProcessingPresent()
193 const {
194 // If echo controller is present, assume it performs active processing.
195 return CaptureMultiBandProcessingActive(/*ec_processing_active=*/true);
196}

198bool AudioProcessingImpl::SubmoduleStates::CaptureMultiBandProcessingActive(
199 bool ec_processing_active) const {
200 return high_pass_filter_enabled_ || mobile_echo_controller_enabled_ ||
201 noise_suppressor_enabled_ || adaptive_gain_controller_enabled_ ||
202 (echo_controller_enabled_ && ec_processing_active);
203}

205bool AudioProcessingImpl::SubmoduleStates::CaptureFullBandProcessingActive()
206 const {
207 return gain_controller2_enabled_ || capture_post_processor_enabled_ ||
208 gain_adjustment_enabled_;

218 adaptive_gain_controller_enabled_ || echo_controller_enabled_;

246AudioProcessingImpl::AudioProcessingImpl(
247 const webrtc::Config& config,
248 std::unique_ptr<CustomProcessing> capture_post_processor,
249 std::unique_ptr<CustomProcessing> render_pre_processor,
250 std::unique_ptr<EchoControlFactory> echo_control_factory,
251 rtc::scoped_refptr<EchoDetector> echo_detector,
252 std::unique_ptr<CustomAudioAnalyzer> capture_analyzer)
253 : data_dumper_(
254 new ApmDataDumper(rtc::AtomicOps::Increment(&instance_count_))),
255 use_setup_specific_default_aec3_config_(
256 UseSetupSpecificDefaultAec3Congfig()),
257 capture_runtime_settings_(RuntimeSettingQueueSize()),
258 render_runtime_settings_(RuntimeSettingQueueSize()),
259 capture_runtime_settings_enqueuer_(&capture_runtime_settings_),
260 render_runtime_settings_enqueuer_(&render_runtime_settings_),
261 echo_control_factory_(std::move(echo_control_factory)),
262 submodule_states_(!!capture_post_processor,
263 !!render_pre_processor,
264 !!capture_analyzer),
265 submodules_(std::move(capture_post_processor),
266 std::move(render_pre_processor),
267 std::move(echo_detector),
268 std::move(capture_analyzer)),
269 constants_(!field_trial::IsEnabled(
270 "WebRTC-ApmExperimentalMultiChannelRenderKillSwitch"),
271 !field_trial::IsEnabled(
272 "WebRTC-ApmExperimentalMultiChannelCaptureKillSwitch"),
273 EnforceSplitBandHpf(),
274 MinimizeProcessingForUnusedOutput(),
275 field_trial::IsEnabled("WebRTC-TransientSuppressorForcedOff")),
276 capture_(),
277 capture_nonlocked_() {
278 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Injected APM submodules:"
279 "\nEcho control factory: "
280 << !!echo_control_factory_
281 << "\nEcho detector: " << !!submodules_.echo_detector
282 << "\nCapture analyzer: " << !!submodules_.capture_analyzer
283 << "\nCapture post processor: "
284 << !!submodules_.capture_post_processor
285 << "\nRender pre processor: "
286 << !!submodules_.render_pre_processor;
287
288 // Mark Echo Controller enabled if a factory is injected.
289 capture_nonlocked_.echo_controller_enabled =
290 static_cast<bool>(echo_control_factory_);
291
292 // If no echo detector is injected, use the ResidualEchoDetector.
293 if (!submodules_.echo_detector) {
294 submodules_.echo_detector = rtc::make_ref_counted<ResidualEchoDetector>();
295 }
296
297#if !(defined(WEBRTC_ANDROID) || defined(WEBRTC_IOS))
298 // TODO(webrtc:5298): Remove once the use of ExperimentalNs has been
299 // deprecated.
300 config_.transient_suppression.enabled = config.Get<ExperimentalNs>().enabled;
301
302 // TODO(webrtc:5298): Remove once the use of ExperimentalAgc has been
303 // deprecated.
304 config_.gain_controller1.analog_gain_controller.enabled =
305 config.Get<ExperimentalAgc>().enabled;
306 config_.gain_controller1.analog_gain_controller.startup_min_volume =
307 config.Get<ExperimentalAgc>().startup_min_volume;
308 config_.gain_controller1.analog_gain_controller.clipped_level_min =
309 config.Get<ExperimentalAgc>().clipped_level_min;
310 config_.gain_controller1.analog_gain_controller.enable_digital_adaptive =
311 !config.Get<ExperimentalAgc>().digital_adaptive_disabled;
312#endif
313
314 Initialize();
315}

319int AudioProcessingImpl::Initialize() {
320 // Run in a single-threaded manner during initialization.
321 MutexLock lock_render(&mutex_render_);
322 MutexLock lock_capture(&mutex_capture_);
323 InitializeLocked();
324 return kNoError;
325}

327int AudioProcessingImpl::Initialize(int capture_input_sample_rate_hz,
328 int capture_output_sample_rate_hz,
329 int render_input_sample_rate_hz,
330 ChannelLayout capture_input_layout,
331 ChannelLayout capture_output_layout,
332 ChannelLayout render_input_layout) {
333 const ProcessingConfig processing_config = {
334 {{capture_input_sample_rate_hz, ChannelsFromLayout(capture_input_layout),
335 LayoutHasKeyboard(capture_input_layout)},
336 {capture_output_sample_rate_hz,
337 ChannelsFromLayout(capture_output_layout),
338 LayoutHasKeyboard(capture_output_layout)},
339 {render_input_sample_rate_hz, ChannelsFromLayout(render_input_layout),
340 LayoutHasKeyboard(render_input_layout)},
341 {render_input_sample_rate_hz, ChannelsFromLayout(render_input_layout),
342 LayoutHasKeyboard(render_input_layout)}}};
343
344 return Initialize(processing_config);
345}

347int AudioProcessingImpl::Initialize(const ProcessingConfig& processing_config) {

350 MutexLock lock_capture(&mutex_capture_);
351 return InitializeLocked(processing_config);

354int AudioProcessingImpl::MaybeInitializeRender(
355 const ProcessingConfig& processing_config) {
356 // Called from both threads. Thread check is therefore not possible.
357 if (processing_config == formats_.api_format) {
358 return kNoError;
359 }
360
361 MutexLock lock_capture(&mutex_capture_);
362 return InitializeLocked(processing_config);
363}
364
365void AudioProcessingImpl::InitializeLocked() {
366 UpdateActiveSubmoduleStates();
367
368 const int render_audiobuffer_sample_rate_hz =
369 formats_.api_format.reverse_output_stream().num_frames() == 0
370 ? formats_.render_processing_format.sample_rate_hz()
371 : formats_.api_format.reverse_output_stream().sample_rate_hz();
372 if (formats_.api_format.reverse_input_stream().num_channels() > 0) {
373 render_.render_audio.reset(new AudioBuffer(
374 formats_.api_format.reverse_input_stream().sample_rate_hz(),
375 formats_.api_format.reverse_input_stream().num_channels(),
376 formats_.render_processing_format.sample_rate_hz(),
377 formats_.render_processing_format.num_channels(),
378 render_audiobuffer_sample_rate_hz,
379 formats_.render_processing_format.num_channels()));
380 if (formats_.api_format.reverse_input_stream() !=
381 formats_.api_format.reverse_output_stream()) {
382 render_.render_converter = AudioConverter::Create(
383 formats_.api_format.reverse_input_stream().num_channels(),
384 formats_.api_format.reverse_input_stream().num_frames(),
385 formats_.api_format.reverse_output_stream().num_channels(),
386 formats_.api_format.reverse_output_stream().num_frames());
387 } else {
388 render_.render_converter.reset(nullptr);
389 }
390 } else {
391 render_.render_audio.reset(nullptr);
392 render_.render_converter.reset(nullptr);
393 }
394
395 capture_.capture_audio.reset(new AudioBuffer(
396 formats_.api_format.input_stream().sample_rate_hz(),
397 formats_.api_format.input_stream().num_channels(),
398 capture_nonlocked_.capture_processing_format.sample_rate_hz(),
399 formats_.api_format.output_stream().num_channels(),
400 formats_.api_format.output_stream().sample_rate_hz(),
401 formats_.api_format.output_stream().num_channels()));
402
403 if (capture_nonlocked_.capture_processing_format.sample_rate_hz() <
404 formats_.api_format.output_stream().sample_rate_hz() &&
405 formats_.api_format.output_stream().sample_rate_hz() == 48000) {
406 capture_.capture_fullband_audio.reset(
407 new AudioBuffer(formats_.api_format.input_stream().sample_rate_hz(),
408 formats_.api_format.input_stream().num_channels(),
409 formats_.api_format.output_stream().sample_rate_hz(),
410 formats_.api_format.output_stream().num_channels(),
411 formats_.api_format.output_stream().sample_rate_hz(),
412 formats_.api_format.output_stream().num_channels()));
413 } else {
414 capture_.capture_fullband_audio.reset();
415 }
416
417 AllocateRenderQueue();
418
419 InitializeGainController1();
420 InitializeTransientSuppressor();
421 InitializeHighPassFilter(true);
422 InitializeVoiceDetector();
423 InitializeResidualEchoDetector();
424 InitializeEchoController();
425 InitializeGainController2();
426 InitializeNoiseSuppressor();
427 InitializeAnalyzer();
428 InitializePostProcessor();
429 InitializePreProcessor();
430 InitializeCaptureLevelsAdjuster();
431
432 if (aec_dump_) {
433 aec_dump_->WriteInitMessage(formats_.api_format, rtc::TimeUTCMillis());
434 }
435}
436
437int AudioProcessingImpl::InitializeLocked(const ProcessingConfig& config) {
438 UpdateActiveSubmoduleStates();
439
440 for (const auto& stream : config.streams) {
441 if (stream.num_channels() > 0 && stream.sample_rate_hz() <= 0) {
442 return kBadSampleRateError;
443 }
444 }
445
446 const size_t num_in_channels = config.input_stream().num_channels();
447 const size_t num_out_channels = config.output_stream().num_channels();
448
449 // Need at least one input channel.
450 // Need either one output channel or as many outputs as there are inputs.
451 if (num_in_channels == 0 ||
452 !(num_out_channels == 1 || num_out_channels == num_in_channels)) {
453 return kBadNumberChannelsError;
454 }
455
456 formats_.api_format = config;
457
458 // Choose maximum rate to use for the split filtering.
459 RTC_DCHECK(config_.pipeline.maximum_internal_processing_rate == 48000 ||
460 config_.pipeline.maximum_internal_processing_rate == 32000);
461 int max_splitting_rate = 48000;
462 if (config_.pipeline.maximum_internal_processing_rate == 32000) {
463 max_splitting_rate = config_.pipeline.maximum_internal_processing_rate;
464 }
465
466 int capture_processing_rate = SuitableProcessRate(
467 std::min(formats_.api_format.input_stream().sample_rate_hz(),
468 formats_.api_format.output_stream().sample_rate_hz()),
469 max_splitting_rate,
470 submodule_states_.CaptureMultiBandSubModulesActive() ||
471 submodule_states_.RenderMultiBandSubModulesActive());
472 RTC_DCHECK_NE(8000, capture_processing_rate);
473
474 capture_nonlocked_.capture_processing_format =
475 StreamConfig(capture_processing_rate);
476
477 int render_processing_rate;
478 if (!capture_nonlocked_.echo_controller_enabled) {
479 render_processing_rate = SuitableProcessRate(
480 std::min(formats_.api_format.reverse_input_stream().sample_rate_hz(),
481 formats_.api_format.reverse_output_stream().sample_rate_hz()),
482 max_splitting_rate,
483 submodule_states_.CaptureMultiBandSubModulesActive() ||
484 submodule_states_.RenderMultiBandSubModulesActive());
485 } else {
486 render_processing_rate = capture_processing_rate;
487 }
488
489 // If the forward sample rate is 8 kHz, the render stream is also processed
490 // at this rate.
491 if (capture_nonlocked_.capture_processing_format.sample_rate_hz() ==
492 kSampleRate8kHz) {
493 render_processing_rate = kSampleRate8kHz;
494 } else {
495 render_processing_rate =
496 std::max(render_processing_rate, static_cast<int>(kSampleRate16kHz));
497 }
498
499 RTC_DCHECK_NE(8000, render_processing_rate);
500
501 if (submodule_states_.RenderMultiBandSubModulesActive()) {
502 // By default, downmix the render stream to mono for analysis. This has been
503 // demonstrated to work well for AEC in most practical scenarios.
504 const bool multi_channel_render = config_.pipeline.multi_channel_render &&
505 constants_.multi_channel_render_support;
506 int render_processing_num_channels =
507 multi_channel_render
508 ? formats_.api_format.reverse_input_stream().num_channels()
509 : 1;
510 formats_.render_processing_format =
511 StreamConfig(render_processing_rate, render_processing_num_channels);
512 } else {
513 formats_.render_processing_format = StreamConfig(
514 formats_.api_format.reverse_input_stream().sample_rate_hz(),
515 formats_.api_format.reverse_input_stream().num_channels());
516 }
517
518 if (capture_nonlocked_.capture_processing_format.sample_rate_hz() ==
519 kSampleRate32kHz ||
520 capture_nonlocked_.capture_processing_format.sample_rate_hz() ==
521 kSampleRate48kHz) {
522 capture_nonlocked_.split_rate = kSampleRate16kHz;
523 } else {
524 capture_nonlocked_.split_rate =
525 capture_nonlocked_.capture_processing_format.sample_rate_hz();
526 }
527
528 InitializeLocked();
529 return kNoError;
530}
531
532void AudioProcessingImpl::ApplyConfig(const AudioProcessing::Config& config) {
533 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "AudioProcessing::ApplyConfig: " << config.ToString();
534
535 // Run in a single-threaded manner when applying the settings.
536 MutexLock lock_render(&mutex_render_);
537 MutexLock lock_capture(&mutex_capture_);
538
539 const bool pipeline_config_changed =
540 config_.pipeline.multi_channel_render !=
541 config.pipeline.multi_channel_render ||
542 config_.pipeline.multi_channel_capture !=
543 config.pipeline.multi_channel_capture ||
544 config_.pipeline.maximum_internal_processing_rate !=
545 config.pipeline.maximum_internal_processing_rate;
546
547 const bool aec_config_changed =
548 config_.echo_canceller.enabled != config.echo_canceller.enabled ||
549 config_.echo_canceller.mobile_mode != config.echo_canceller.mobile_mode;
550
551 const bool agc1_config_changed =
552 config_.gain_controller1 != config.gain_controller1;
553
554 const bool agc2_config_changed =
555 config_.gain_controller2 != config.gain_controller2;
556
557 const bool voice_detection_config_changed =
558 config_.voice_detection.enabled != config.voice_detection.enabled;
559
560 const bool ns_config_changed =
561 config_.noise_suppression.enabled != config.noise_suppression.enabled ||
562 config_.noise_suppression.level != config.noise_suppression.level;
563
564 const bool ts_config_changed = config_.transient_suppression.enabled !=
565 config.transient_suppression.enabled;
566
567 const bool pre_amplifier_config_changed =
568 config_.pre_amplifier.enabled != config.pre_amplifier.enabled ||
569 config_.pre_amplifier.fixed_gain_factor !=
570 config.pre_amplifier.fixed_gain_factor;
571
572 const bool gain_adjustment_config_changed =
573 config_.capture_level_adjustment != config.capture_level_adjustment;
574
575 config_ = config;
576
577 if (aec_config_changed) {
578 InitializeEchoController();
579 }
580
581 if (ns_config_changed) {
582 InitializeNoiseSuppressor();
583 }
584
585 if (ts_config_changed) {
586 InitializeTransientSuppressor();
587 }
588
589 InitializeHighPassFilter(false);
590
591 if (agc1_config_changed) {
592 InitializeGainController1();
593 }
594
595 const bool config_ok = GainController2::Validate(config_.gain_controller2);
596 if (!config_ok) {
597 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR)
598 << "Invalid Gain Controller 2 config; using the default config.";
599 config_.gain_controller2 = AudioProcessing::Config::GainController2();
600 }
601
602 if (agc2_config_changed) {
603 InitializeGainController2();
604 }
605
606 if (pre_amplifier_config_changed || gain_adjustment_config_changed) {
607 InitializeCaptureLevelsAdjuster();
608 }
609
610 if (config_.level_estimation.enabled && !submodules_.output_level_estimator) {
611 submodules_.output_level_estimator = std::make_unique<LevelEstimator>();
612 }
613
614 if (voice_detection_config_changed) {
615 InitializeVoiceDetector();
616 }
617
618 // Reinitialization must happen after all submodule configuration to avoid
619 // additional reinitializations on the next capture / render processing call.
620 if (pipeline_config_changed) {
621 InitializeLocked(formats_.api_format);
622 }
623}

656
657size_t AudioProcessingImpl::num_proc_channels() const {
658 // Used as callback from submodules, hence locking is not allowed.
659 const bool multi_channel_capture = config_.pipeline.multi_channel_capture &&
660 constants_.multi_channel_capture_support;
661 if (capture_nonlocked_.echo_controller_enabled && !multi_channel_capture) {
662 return 1;
663 }
664 return num_output_channels();
665}

667size_t AudioProcessingImpl::num_output_channels() const {
668 // Used as callback from submodules, hence locking is not allowed.
669 return formats_.api_format.output_stream().num_channels();
670}

696void AudioProcessingImpl::SetRuntimeSetting(RuntimeSetting setting) {
697 PostRuntimeSetting(setting);

699
700bool AudioProcessingImpl::PostRuntimeSetting(RuntimeSetting setting) {
701 switch (setting.type()) {
702 case RuntimeSetting::Type::kCustomRenderProcessingRuntimeSetting:
703 case RuntimeSetting::Type::kPlayoutAudioDeviceChange:
704 return render_runtime_settings_enqueuer_.Enqueue(setting);
705 case RuntimeSetting::Type::kCapturePreGain:
706 case RuntimeSetting::Type::kCapturePostGain:
707 case RuntimeSetting::Type::kCaptureCompressionGain:
708 case RuntimeSetting::Type::kCaptureFixedPostGain:
709 case RuntimeSetting::Type::kCaptureOutputUsed:
710 return capture_runtime_settings_enqueuer_.Enqueue(setting);
711 case RuntimeSetting::Type::kPlayoutVolumeChange: {
712 bool enqueueing_successful;
713 enqueueing_successful =
714 capture_runtime_settings_enqueuer_.Enqueue(setting);
715 enqueueing_successful =
716 render_runtime_settings_enqueuer_.Enqueue(setting) &&
717 enqueueing_successful;
718 return enqueueing_successful;
719 }
720 case RuntimeSetting::Type::kNotSpecified:
721 RTC_NOTREACHED();
722 return true;
723 }
724 // The language allows the enum to have a non-enumerator
725 // value. Check that this doesn't happen.
726 RTC_NOTREACHED();
727 return true;
728}

730AudioProcessingImpl::RuntimeSettingEnqueuer::RuntimeSettingEnqueuer(
731 SwapQueue<RuntimeSetting>* runtime_settings)
732 : runtime_settings_(*runtime_settings) {
733 RTC_DCHECK(runtime_settings);
734}
735
736AudioProcessingImpl::RuntimeSettingEnqueuer::~RuntimeSettingEnqueuer() =
737 default;
738
739bool AudioProcessingImpl::RuntimeSettingEnqueuer::Enqueue(
740 RuntimeSetting setting) {
741 const bool successful_insert = runtime_settings_.Insert(&setting);
742
743 if (!successful_insert) {
744 RTC_HISTOGRAM_BOOLEAN("WebRTC.Audio.ApmRuntimeSettingCannotEnqueue", 1);
745 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Cannot enqueue a new runtime setting.";
746 }
747 return successful_insert;
748}
749
750int AudioProcessingImpl::MaybeInitializeCapture(
751 const StreamConfig& input_config,
752 const StreamConfig& output_config) {
753 ProcessingConfig processing_config;
754 bool reinitialization_required = false;
755 {
756 // Acquire the capture lock in order to access api_format. The lock is
757 // released immediately, as we may need to acquire the render lock as part
758 // of the conditional reinitialization.
759 MutexLock lock_capture(&mutex_capture_);
760 processing_config = formats_.api_format;
761 reinitialization_required = UpdateActiveSubmoduleStates();
762 }
763
764 if (processing_config.input_stream() != input_config) {
765 processing_config.input_stream() = input_config;
766 reinitialization_required = true;
767 }
768
769 if (processing_config.output_stream() != output_config) {
770 processing_config.output_stream() = output_config;
771 reinitialization_required = true;
772 }
773
774 if (reinitialization_required) {
775 MutexLock lock_render(&mutex_render_);
776 MutexLock lock_capture(&mutex_capture_);
777 RETURN_ON_ERR(InitializeLocked(processing_config));
778 }
779 return kNoError;
780}
781
782int AudioProcessingImpl::ProcessStream(const float* const* src,
783 const StreamConfig& input_config,
784 const StreamConfig& output_config,
785 float* const* dest) {
786 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "AudioProcessing::ProcessStream_StreamConfig");
787 if (!src || !dest) {
788 return kNullPointerError;
789 }
790
791 RETURN_ON_ERR(MaybeInitializeCapture(input_config, output_config));
792
793 MutexLock lock_capture(&mutex_capture_);
794
795 if (aec_dump_) {
796 RecordUnprocessedCaptureStream(src);
797 }
798
799 capture_.keyboard_info.Extract(src, formats_.api_format.input_stream());
800 capture_.capture_audio->CopyFrom(src, formats_.api_format.input_stream());
801 if (capture_.capture_fullband_audio) {
802 capture_.capture_fullband_audio->CopyFrom(
803 src, formats_.api_format.input_stream());
804 }
805 RETURN_ON_ERR(ProcessCaptureStreamLocked());
806 if (capture_.capture_fullband_audio) {
807 capture_.capture_fullband_audio->CopyTo(formats_.api_format.output_stream(),
808 dest);
809 } else {
810 capture_.capture_audio->CopyTo(formats_.api_format.output_stream(), dest);
811 }
812
813 if (aec_dump_) {
814 RecordProcessedCaptureStream(dest);
815 }
816 return kNoError;
817}
818
819void AudioProcessingImpl::HandleCaptureRuntimeSettings() {
820 RuntimeSetting setting;
821 int num_settings_processed = 0;
822 while (capture_runtime_settings_.Remove(&setting)) {
823 if (aec_dump_) {
824 aec_dump_->WriteRuntimeSetting(setting);
825 }
826 switch (setting.type()) {
827 case RuntimeSetting::Type::kCapturePreGain:
828 if (config_.pre_amplifier.enabled ||
829 config_.capture_level_adjustment.enabled) {
830 float value;
831 setting.GetFloat(&value);
832 // If the pre-amplifier is used, apply the new gain to the
833 // pre-amplifier regardless if the capture level adjustment is
834 // activated. This approach allows both functionalities to coexist
835 // until they have been properly merged.
836 if (config_.pre_amplifier.enabled) {
837 config_.pre_amplifier.fixed_gain_factor = value;
838 } else {
839 config_.capture_level_adjustment.pre_gain_factor = value;
840 }
841
842 // Use both the pre-amplifier and the capture level adjustment gains
843 // as pre-gains.
844 float gain = 1.f;
845 if (config_.pre_amplifier.enabled) {
846 gain *= config_.pre_amplifier.fixed_gain_factor;
847 }
848 if (config_.capture_level_adjustment.enabled) {
849 gain *= config_.capture_level_adjustment.pre_gain_factor;
850 }
851
852 submodules_.capture_levels_adjuster->SetPreGain(gain);
853 }
854 // TODO(bugs.chromium.org/9138): Log setting handling by Aec Dump.
855 break;
856 case RuntimeSetting::Type::kCapturePostGain:
857 if (config_.capture_level_adjustment.enabled) {
858 float value;
859 setting.GetFloat(&value);
860 config_.capture_level_adjustment.post_gain_factor = value;
861 submodules_.capture_levels_adjuster->SetPostGain(
862 config_.capture_level_adjustment.post_gain_factor);
863 }
864 // TODO(bugs.chromium.org/9138): Log setting handling by Aec Dump.
865 break;
866 case RuntimeSetting::Type::kCaptureCompressionGain: {
867 if (!submodules_.agc_manager) {
868 float value;
869 setting.GetFloat(&value);
870 int int_value = static_cast<int>(value + .5f);
871 config_.gain_controller1.compression_gain_db = int_value;
872 if (submodules_.gain_control) {
873 int error =
874 submodules_.gain_control->set_compression_gain_db(int_value);
875 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(kNoError, error);
876 }
877 }
878 break;
879 }
880 case RuntimeSetting::Type::kCaptureFixedPostGain: {
881 if (submodules_.gain_controller2) {
882 float value;
883 setting.GetFloat(&value);
884 config_.gain_controller2.fixed_digital.gain_db = value;
885 submodules_.gain_controller2->ApplyConfig(config_.gain_controller2);
886 }
887 break;
888 }
889 case RuntimeSetting::Type::kPlayoutVolumeChange: {
890 int value;
891 setting.GetInt(&value);
892 capture_.playout_volume = value;
893 break;
894 }
895 case RuntimeSetting::Type::kPlayoutAudioDeviceChange:
896 RTC_NOTREACHED();
897 break;
898 case RuntimeSetting::Type::kCustomRenderProcessingRuntimeSetting:
899 RTC_NOTREACHED();
900 break;
901 case RuntimeSetting::Type::kNotSpecified:
902 RTC_NOTREACHED();
903 break;
904 case RuntimeSetting::Type::kCaptureOutputUsed:
905 bool value;
906 setting.GetBool(&value);
907 HandleCaptureOutputUsedSetting(value);
908 break;
909 }
910 ++num_settings_processed;
911 }
912
913 if (num_settings_processed >= RuntimeSettingQueueSize()) {
914 // Handle overrun of the runtime settings queue, which likely will has
915 // caused settings to be discarded.
916 HandleOverrunInCaptureRuntimeSettingsQueue();
917 }
918}
919
920void AudioProcessingImpl::HandleOverrunInCaptureRuntimeSettingsQueue() {
921 // Fall back to a safe state for the case when a setting for capture output
922 // usage setting has been missed.
923 HandleCaptureOutputUsedSetting(/*capture_output_used=*/true);
924}
925
926void AudioProcessingImpl::HandleRenderRuntimeSettings() {
927 RuntimeSetting setting;
928 while (render_runtime_settings_.Remove(&setting)) {
929 if (aec_dump_) {
930 aec_dump_->WriteRuntimeSetting(setting);
931 }
932 switch (setting.type()) {
933 case RuntimeSetting::Type::kPlayoutAudioDeviceChange: // fall-through
934 case RuntimeSetting::Type::kPlayoutVolumeChange: // fall-through
935 case RuntimeSetting::Type::kCustomRenderProcessingRuntimeSetting:
936 if (submodules_.render_pre_processor) {
937 submodules_.render_pre_processor->SetRuntimeSetting(setting);
938 }
939 break;
940 case RuntimeSetting::Type::kCapturePreGain: // fall-through
941 case RuntimeSetting::Type::kCapturePostGain: // fall-through
942 case RuntimeSetting::Type::kCaptureCompressionGain: // fall-through
943 case RuntimeSetting::Type::kCaptureFixedPostGain: // fall-through
944 case RuntimeSetting::Type::kCaptureOutputUsed: // fall-through
945 case RuntimeSetting::Type::kNotSpecified:
946 RTC_NOTREACHED();
947 break;
948 }
949 }
950}
951
952void AudioProcessingImpl::QueueBandedRenderAudio(AudioBuffer* audio) {
953 RTC_DCHECK_GE(160, audio->num_frames_per_band());
954
955 if (submodules_.echo_control_mobile) {
956 EchoControlMobileImpl::PackRenderAudioBuffer(audio, num_output_channels(),
957 num_reverse_channels(),
958 &aecm_render_queue_buffer_);
959 RTC_DCHECK(aecm_render_signal_queue_);
960 // Insert the samples into the queue.
961 if (!aecm_render_signal_queue_->Insert(&aecm_render_queue_buffer_)) {
962 // The data queue is full and needs to be emptied.
963 EmptyQueuedRenderAudio();
964
965 // Retry the insert (should always work).
966 bool result =
967 aecm_render_signal_queue_->Insert(&aecm_render_queue_buffer_);
968 RTC_DCHECK(result);
969 }
970 }
971
972 if (!submodules_.agc_manager && submodules_.gain_control) {
973 GainControlImpl::PackRenderAudioBuffer(*audio, &agc_render_queue_buffer_);
974 // Insert the samples into the queue.
975 if (!agc_render_signal_queue_->Insert(&agc_render_queue_buffer_)) {
976 // The data queue is full and needs to be emptied.
977 EmptyQueuedRenderAudio();
978
979 // Retry the insert (should always work).
980 bool result = agc_render_signal_queue_->Insert(&agc_render_queue_buffer_);
981 RTC_DCHECK(result);
982 }
983 }
984}
985
986void AudioProcessingImpl::QueueNonbandedRenderAudio(AudioBuffer* audio) {
987 ResidualEchoDetector::PackRenderAudioBuffer(audio, &red_render_queue_buffer_);
988
989 // Insert the samples into the queue.
990 if (!red_render_signal_queue_->Insert(&red_render_queue_buffer_)) {
991 // The data queue is full and needs to be emptied.
992 EmptyQueuedRenderAudio();
993
994 // Retry the insert (should always work).
995 bool result = red_render_signal_queue_->Insert(&red_render_queue_buffer_);
996 RTC_DCHECK(result);
997 }
998}
999
1000void AudioProcessingImpl::AllocateRenderQueue() {
1001 const size_t new_agc_render_queue_element_max_size =
1002 std::max(static_cast<size_t>(1), kMaxAllowedValuesOfSamplesPerBand);
1003
1004 const size_t new_red_render_queue_element_max_size =
1005 std::max(static_cast<size_t>(1), kMaxAllowedValuesOfSamplesPerFrame);
1006
1007 // Reallocate the queues if the queue item sizes are too small to fit the
1008 // data to put in the queues.
1009
1010 if (agc_render_queue_element_max_size_ <
1011 new_agc_render_queue_element_max_size) {
1012 agc_render_queue_element_max_size_ = new_agc_render_queue_element_max_size;
1013
1014 std::vector<int16_t> template_queue_element(
1015 agc_render_queue_element_max_size_);
1016
1017 agc_render_signal_queue_.reset(
1018 new SwapQueue<std::vector<int16_t>, RenderQueueItemVerifier<int16_t>>(
1019 kMaxNumFramesToBuffer, template_queue_element,
1020 RenderQueueItemVerifier<int16_t>(
1021 agc_render_queue_element_max_size_)));
1022
1023 agc_render_queue_buffer_.resize(agc_render_queue_element_max_size_);
1024 agc_capture_queue_buffer_.resize(agc_render_queue_element_max_size_);
1025 } else {
1026 agc_render_signal_queue_->Clear();
1027 }
1028
1029 if (red_render_queue_element_max_size_ <
1030 new_red_render_queue_element_max_size) {
1031 red_render_queue_element_max_size_ = new_red_render_queue_element_max_size;
1032
1033 std::vector<float> template_queue_element(
1034 red_render_queue_element_max_size_);
1035
1036 red_render_signal_queue_.reset(
1037 new SwapQueue<std::vector<float>, RenderQueueItemVerifier<float>>(
1038 kMaxNumFramesToBuffer, template_queue_element,
1039 RenderQueueItemVerifier<float>(
1040 red_render_queue_element_max_size_)));
1041
1042 red_render_queue_buffer_.resize(red_render_queue_element_max_size_);
1043 red_capture_queue_buffer_.resize(red_render_queue_element_max_size_);
1044 } else {
1045 red_render_signal_queue_->Clear();
1046 }
1047}
1048
1049void AudioProcessingImpl::EmptyQueuedRenderAudio() {
1050 MutexLock lock_capture(&mutex_capture_);
1051 EmptyQueuedRenderAudioLocked();
1052}
1053
1054void AudioProcessingImpl::EmptyQueuedRenderAudioLocked() {
1055 if (submodules_.echo_control_mobile) {
1056 RTC_DCHECK(aecm_render_signal_queue_);
1057 while (aecm_render_signal_queue_->Remove(&aecm_capture_queue_buffer_)) {
1058 submodules_.echo_control_mobile->ProcessRenderAudio(
1059 aecm_capture_queue_buffer_);
1060 }
1061 }
1062
1063 if (submodules_.gain_control) {
1064 while (agc_render_signal_queue_->Remove(&agc_capture_queue_buffer_)) {
1065 submodules_.gain_control->ProcessRenderAudio(agc_capture_queue_buffer_);
1066 }
1067 }
1068
1069 while (red_render_signal_queue_->Remove(&red_capture_queue_buffer_)) {
1070 RTC_DCHECK(submodules_.echo_detector);
1071 submodules_.echo_detector->AnalyzeRenderAudio(red_capture_queue_buffer_);
1072 }
1073}
1074
1075int AudioProcessingImpl::ProcessStream(const int16_t* const src,
1076 const StreamConfig& input_config,
1077 const StreamConfig& output_config,
1078 int16_t* const dest) {
1079 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "AudioProcessing::ProcessStream_AudioFrame");
1080 RETURN_ON_ERR(MaybeInitializeCapture(input_config, output_config));
1081
1082 MutexLock lock_capture(&mutex_capture_);
1083
1084 if (aec_dump_) {
1085 RecordUnprocessedCaptureStream(src, input_config);
1086 }
1087
1088 capture_.capture_audio->CopyFrom(src, input_config);
1089 if (capture_.capture_fullband_audio) {
1090 capture_.capture_fullband_audio->CopyFrom(src, input_config);
1091 }
1092 RETURN_ON_ERR(ProcessCaptureStreamLocked());
1093 if (submodule_states_.CaptureMultiBandProcessingPresent() ||
1094 submodule_states_.CaptureFullBandProcessingActive()) {
1095 if (capture_.capture_fullband_audio) {
1096 capture_.capture_fullband_audio->CopyTo(output_config, dest);
1097 } else {
1098 capture_.capture_audio->CopyTo(output_config, dest);
1099 }
1100 }
1101
1102 if (aec_dump_) {
1103 RecordProcessedCaptureStream(dest, output_config);
1104 }
1105
1106 return kNoError;
1107}
1108
1109int AudioProcessingImpl::ProcessCaptureStreamLocked() {
1110 EmptyQueuedRenderAudioLocked();
1111 HandleCaptureRuntimeSettings();
1112
1113 // Ensure that not both the AEC and AECM are active at the same time.
1114 // TODO(peah): Simplify once the public API Enable functions for these
1115 // are moved to APM.
1116 RTC_DCHECK_LE(
1117 !!submodules_.echo_controller + !!submodules_.echo_control_mobile, 1);
1118
1119 AudioBuffer* capture_buffer = capture_.capture_audio.get(); // For brevity.
1120 AudioBuffer* linear_aec_buffer = capture_.linear_aec_output.get();
1121
1122 if (submodules_.high_pass_filter &&
1123 config_.high_pass_filter.apply_in_full_band &&
1124 !constants_.enforce_split_band_hpf) {
1125 submodules_.high_pass_filter->Process(capture_buffer,
1126 /*use_split_band_data=*/false);
1127 }
1128
1129 if (submodules_.capture_levels_adjuster) {
1130 // If the analog mic gain emulation is active, get the emulated analog mic
1131 // gain and pass it to the analog gain control functionality.
1132 if (config_.capture_level_adjustment.analog_mic_gain_emulation.enabled) {
1133 int level = submodules_.capture_levels_adjuster->GetAnalogMicGainLevel();
1134 if (submodules_.agc_manager) {
1135 submodules_.agc_manager->set_stream_analog_level(level);
1136 } else if (submodules_.gain_control) {
1137 int error = submodules_.gain_control->set_stream_analog_level(level);
1138 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(kNoError, error);
1139 }
1140 }
1141
1142 submodules_.capture_levels_adjuster->ApplyPreLevelAdjustment(
1143 *capture_buffer);
1144 }
1145
1146 capture_input_rms_.Analyze(rtc::ArrayView<const float>(
1147 capture_buffer->channels_const()[0],
1148 capture_nonlocked_.capture_processing_format.num_frames()));
1149 const bool log_rms = ++capture_rms_interval_counter_ >= 1000;
1150 if (log_rms) {
1151 capture_rms_interval_counter_ = 0;
1152 RmsLevel::Levels levels = capture_input_rms_.AverageAndPeak();
1153 RTC_HISTOGRAM_COUNTS_LINEAR("WebRTC.Audio.ApmCaptureInputLevelAverageRms",
1154 levels.average, 1, RmsLevel::kMinLevelDb, 64);
1155 RTC_HISTOGRAM_COUNTS_LINEAR("WebRTC.Audio.ApmCaptureInputLevelPeakRms",
1156 levels.peak, 1, RmsLevel::kMinLevelDb, 64);
1157 }
1158
1159 if (submodules_.echo_controller) {
1160 // Detect and flag any change in the analog gain.
1161 int analog_mic_level = recommended_stream_analog_level_locked();
1162 capture_.echo_path_gain_change =
1163 capture_.prev_analog_mic_level != analog_mic_level &&
1164 capture_.prev_analog_mic_level != -1;
1165 capture_.prev_analog_mic_level = analog_mic_level;
1166
1167 // Detect and flag any change in the capture level adjustment pre-gain.
1168 if (submodules_.capture_levels_adjuster) {
1169 float pre_adjustment_gain =
1170 submodules_.capture_levels_adjuster->GetPreAdjustmentGain();
1171 capture_.echo_path_gain_change =
1172 capture_.echo_path_gain_change ||
1173 (capture_.prev_pre_adjustment_gain != pre_adjustment_gain &&
1174 capture_.prev_pre_adjustment_gain >= 0.f);
1175 capture_.prev_pre_adjustment_gain = pre_adjustment_gain;
1176 }
1177
1178 // Detect volume change.
1179 capture_.echo_path_gain_change =
1180 capture_.echo_path_gain_change ||
1181 (capture_.prev_playout_volume != capture_.playout_volume &&
1182 capture_.prev_playout_volume >= 0);
1183 capture_.prev_playout_volume = capture_.playout_volume;
1184
1185 submodules_.echo_controller->AnalyzeCapture(capture_buffer);
1186 }
1187
1188 if (submodules_.agc_manager) {
1189 submodules_.agc_manager->AnalyzePreProcess(capture_buffer);
1190 }
1191
1192 if (submodule_states_.CaptureMultiBandSubModulesActive() &&
1193 SampleRateSupportsMultiBand(
1194 capture_nonlocked_.capture_processing_format.sample_rate_hz())) {
1195 capture_buffer->SplitIntoFrequencyBands();
1196 }
1197
1198 const bool multi_channel_capture = config_.pipeline.multi_channel_capture &&
1199 constants_.multi_channel_capture_support;
1200 if (submodules_.echo_controller && !multi_channel_capture) {
1201 // Force down-mixing of the number of channels after the detection of
1202 // capture signal saturation.
1203 // TODO(peah): Look into ensuring that this kind of tampering with the
1204 // AudioBuffer functionality should not be needed.
1205 capture_buffer->set_num_channels(1);
1206 }
1207
1208 if (submodules_.high_pass_filter &&
1209 (!config_.high_pass_filter.apply_in_full_band ||
1210 constants_.enforce_split_band_hpf)) {
1211 submodules_.high_pass_filter->Process(capture_buffer,
1212 /*use_split_band_data=*/true);
1213 }
1214
1215 if (submodules_.gain_control) {
1216 RETURN_ON_ERR(
1217 submodules_.gain_control->AnalyzeCaptureAudio(*capture_buffer));
1218 }
1219
1220 if ((!config_.noise_suppression.analyze_linear_aec_output_when_available ||
1221 !linear_aec_buffer || submodules_.echo_control_mobile) &&
1222 submodules_.noise_suppressor) {
1223 submodules_.noise_suppressor->Analyze(*capture_buffer);
1224 }
1225
1226 if (submodules_.echo_control_mobile) {
1227 // Ensure that the stream delay was set before the call to the
1228 // AECM ProcessCaptureAudio function.
1229 if (!capture_.was_stream_delay_set) {
1230 return AudioProcessing::kStreamParameterNotSetError;
1231 }
1232
1233 if (submodules_.noise_suppressor) {
1234 submodules_.noise_suppressor->Process(capture_buffer);
1235 }
1236
1237 RETURN_ON_ERR(submodules_.echo_control_mobile->ProcessCaptureAudio(
1238 capture_buffer, stream_delay_ms()));
1239 } else {
1240 if (submodules_.echo_controller) {
1241 data_dumper_->DumpRaw("stream_delay", stream_delay_ms());
1242
1243 if (capture_.was_stream_delay_set) {
1244 submodules_.echo_controller->SetAudioBufferDelay(stream_delay_ms());
1245 }
1246
1247 submodules_.echo_controller->ProcessCapture(
1248 capture_buffer, linear_aec_buffer, capture_.echo_path_gain_change);
1249 }
1250
1251 if (config_.noise_suppression.analyze_linear_aec_output_when_available &&
1252 linear_aec_buffer && submodules_.noise_suppressor) {
1253 submodules_.noise_suppressor->Analyze(*linear_aec_buffer);
1254 }
1255
1256 if (submodules_.noise_suppressor) {
1257 submodules_.noise_suppressor->Process(capture_buffer);
1258 }
1259 }
1260
1261 if (config_.voice_detection.enabled) {
1262 capture_.stats.voice_detected =
1263 submodules_.voice_detector->ProcessCaptureAudio(capture_buffer);
1264 } else {
1265 capture_.stats.voice_detected = absl::nullopt;
1266 }
1267
1268 if (submodules_.agc_manager) {
1269 submodules_.agc_manager->Process(capture_buffer);
1270
1271 absl::optional<int> new_digital_gain =
1272 submodules_.agc_manager->GetDigitalComressionGain();
1273 if (new_digital_gain && submodules_.gain_control) {
1274 submodules_.gain_control->set_compression_gain_db(*new_digital_gain);
1275 }
1276 }
1277
1278 if (submodules_.gain_control) {
1279 // TODO(peah): Add reporting from AEC3 whether there is echo.
1280 RETURN_ON_ERR(submodules_.gain_control->ProcessCaptureAudio(
1281 capture_buffer, /*stream_has_echo*/ false));
1282 }
1283
1284 if (submodule_states_.CaptureMultiBandProcessingPresent() &&
1285 SampleRateSupportsMultiBand(
1286 capture_nonlocked_.capture_processing_format.sample_rate_hz())) {
1287 capture_buffer->MergeFrequencyBands();
1288 }
1289
1290 capture_.stats.output_rms_dbfs = absl::nullopt;
1291 if (capture_.capture_output_used) {
1292 if (capture_.capture_fullband_audio) {
1293 const auto& ec = submodules_.echo_controller;
1294 bool ec_active = ec ? ec->ActiveProcessing() : false;
1295 // Only update the fullband buffer if the multiband processing has changed
1296 // the signal. Keep the original signal otherwise.
1297 if (submodule_states_.CaptureMultiBandProcessingActive(ec_active)) {
1298 capture_buffer->CopyTo(capture_.capture_fullband_audio.get());
1299 }
1300 capture_buffer = capture_.capture_fullband_audio.get();
1301 }
1302
1303 if (config_.residual_echo_detector.enabled) {
1304 RTC_DCHECK(submodules_.echo_detector);
1305 submodules_.echo_detector->AnalyzeCaptureAudio(
1306 rtc::ArrayView<const float>(capture_buffer->channels()[0],
1307 capture_buffer->num_frames()));
1308 }
1309
1310 // TODO(aluebs): Investigate if the transient suppression placement should
1311 // be before or after the AGC.
1312 if (submodules_.transient_suppressor) {
1313 float voice_probability =
1314 submodules_.agc_manager.get()
1315 ? submodules_.agc_manager->voice_probability()
1316 : 1.f;
1317
1318 submodules_.transient_suppressor->Suppress(
1319 capture_buffer->channels()[0], capture_buffer->num_frames(),
1320 capture_buffer->num_channels(),
1321 capture_buffer->split_bands_const(0)[kBand0To8kHz],
1322 capture_buffer->num_frames_per_band(),
1323 capture_.keyboard_info.keyboard_data,
1324 capture_.keyboard_info.num_keyboard_frames, voice_probability,
1325 capture_.key_pressed);
1326 }
1327
1328 // Experimental APM sub-module that analyzes |capture_buffer|.
1329 if (submodules_.capture_analyzer) {
1330 submodules_.capture_analyzer->Analyze(capture_buffer);
1331 }
1332
1333 if (submodules_.gain_controller2) {
1334 submodules_.gain_controller2->NotifyAnalogLevel(
1335 recommended_stream_analog_level_locked());
1336 submodules_.gain_controller2->Process(capture_buffer);
1337 }
1338
1339 if (submodules_.capture_post_processor) {
1340 submodules_.capture_post_processor->Process(capture_buffer);
1341 }
1342
1343 // The level estimator operates on the recombined data.
1344 if (config_.level_estimation.enabled) {
1345 submodules_.output_level_estimator->ProcessStream(*capture_buffer);
1346 capture_.stats.output_rms_dbfs =
1347 submodules_.output_level_estimator->RMS();
1348 }
1349
1350 capture_output_rms_.Analyze(rtc::ArrayView<const float>(
1351 capture_buffer->channels_const()[0],
1352 capture_nonlocked_.capture_processing_format.num_frames()));
1353 if (log_rms) {
1354 RmsLevel::Levels levels = capture_output_rms_.AverageAndPeak();
1355 RTC_HISTOGRAM_COUNTS_LINEAR(
1356 "WebRTC.Audio.ApmCaptureOutputLevelAverageRms", levels.average, 1,
1357 RmsLevel::kMinLevelDb, 64);
1358 RTC_HISTOGRAM_COUNTS_LINEAR("WebRTC.Audio.ApmCaptureOutputLevelPeakRms",
1359 levels.peak, 1, RmsLevel::kMinLevelDb, 64);
1360 }
1361
1362 if (submodules_.agc_manager) {
1363 int level = recommended_stream_analog_level_locked();
1364 data_dumper_->DumpRaw("experimental_gain_control_stream_analog_level", 1,
1365 &level);
1366 }
1367
1368 // Compute echo-detector stats.
1369 if (config_.residual_echo_detector.enabled) {
1370 RTC_DCHECK(submodules_.echo_detector);
1371 auto ed_metrics = submodules_.echo_detector->GetMetrics();
1372 capture_.stats.residual_echo_likelihood = ed_metrics.echo_likelihood;
1373 capture_.stats.residual_echo_likelihood_recent_max =
1374 ed_metrics.echo_likelihood_recent_max;
1375 }
1376 }
1377
1378 // Compute echo-controller stats.
1379 if (submodules_.echo_controller) {
1380 auto ec_metrics = submodules_.echo_controller->GetMetrics();
1381 capture_.stats.echo_return_loss = ec_metrics.echo_return_loss;
1382 capture_.stats.echo_return_loss_enhancement =
1383 ec_metrics.echo_return_loss_enhancement;
1384 capture_.stats.delay_ms = ec_metrics.delay_ms;
1385 }
1386
1387 // Pass stats for reporting.
1388 stats_reporter_.UpdateStatistics(capture_.stats);
1389
1390 if (submodules_.capture_levels_adjuster) {
1391 submodules_.capture_levels_adjuster->ApplyPostLevelAdjustment(
1392 *capture_buffer);
1393
1394 // If the analog mic gain emulation is active, retrieve the level from the
1395 // analog gain control and set it to mic gain emulator.
1396 if (config_.capture_level_adjustment.analog_mic_gain_emulation.enabled) {
1397 if (submodules_.agc_manager) {
1398 submodules_.capture_levels_adjuster->SetAnalogMicGainLevel(
1399 submodules_.agc_manager->stream_analog_level());
1400 } else if (submodules_.gain_control) {
1401 submodules_.capture_levels_adjuster->SetAnalogMicGainLevel(
1402 submodules_.gain_control->stream_analog_level());
1403 }
1404 }
1405 }
1406
1407 // Temporarily set the output to zero after the stream has been unmuted
1408 // (capture output is again used). The purpose of this is to avoid clicks and
1409 // artefacts in the audio that results when the processing again is
1410 // reactivated after unmuting.
1411 if (!capture_.capture_output_used_last_frame &&
1412 capture_.capture_output_used) {
1413 for (size_t ch = 0; ch < capture_buffer->num_channels(); ++ch) {
1414 rtc::ArrayView<float> channel_view(capture_buffer->channels()[ch],
1415 capture_buffer->num_frames());
1416 std::fill(channel_view.begin(), channel_view.end(), 0.f);
1417 }
1418 }
1419 capture_.capture_output_used_last_frame = capture_.capture_output_used;
1420
1421 capture_.was_stream_delay_set = false;
1422 return kNoError;
1423}

1425int AudioProcessingImpl::AnalyzeReverseStream(
1426 const float* const* data,
1427 const StreamConfig& reverse_config) {
1428 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "AudioProcessing::AnalyzeReverseStream_StreamConfig");
1429 MutexLock lock(&mutex_render_);
1430 return AnalyzeReverseStreamLocked(data, reverse_config, reverse_config);
1431}
1432
1433int AudioProcessingImpl::ProcessReverseStream(const float* const* src,
1434 const StreamConfig& input_config,
1435 const StreamConfig& output_config,
1436 float* const* dest) {
1437 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "AudioProcessing::ProcessReverseStream_StreamConfig");
1438 MutexLock lock(&mutex_render_);
1439 RETURN_ON_ERR(AnalyzeReverseStreamLocked(src, input_config, output_config));
1440 if (submodule_states_.RenderMultiBandProcessingActive() ||
1441 submodule_states_.RenderFullBandProcessingActive()) {
1442 render_.render_audio->CopyTo(formats_.api_format.reverse_output_stream(),
1443 dest);
1444 } else if (formats_.api_format.reverse_input_stream() !=
1445 formats_.api_format.reverse_output_stream()) {
1446 render_.render_converter->Convert(src, input_config.num_samples(), dest,
1447 output_config.num_samples());
1448 } else {
1449 CopyAudioIfNeeded(src, input_config.num_frames(),
1450 input_config.num_channels(), dest);
1451 }
1452
1453 return kNoError;
1454}
1455
1456int AudioProcessingImpl::AnalyzeReverseStreamLocked(
1457 const float* const* src,
1458 const StreamConfig& input_config,
1459 const StreamConfig& output_config) {
1460 if (src == nullptr) {
1461 return kNullPointerError;
1462 }
1463
1464 if (input_config.num_channels() == 0) {
1465 return kBadNumberChannelsError;
1466 }
1467
1468 ProcessingConfig processing_config = formats_.api_format;
1469 processing_config.reverse_input_stream() = input_config;
1470 processing_config.reverse_output_stream() = output_config;
1471
1472 RETURN_ON_ERR(MaybeInitializeRender(processing_config));
1473 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(input_config.num_frames(),
1474 formats_.api_format.reverse_input_stream().num_frames());
1475
1476 if (aec_dump_) {
1477 const size_t channel_size =
1478 formats_.api_format.reverse_input_stream().num_frames();
1479 const size_t num_channels =
1480 formats_.api_format.reverse_input_stream().num_channels();
1481 aec_dump_->WriteRenderStreamMessage(
1482 AudioFrameView<const float>(src, num_channels, channel_size));
1483 }
1484 render_.render_audio->CopyFrom(src,
1485 formats_.api_format.reverse_input_stream());
1486 return ProcessRenderStreamLocked();
1487}
1488
1489int AudioProcessingImpl::ProcessReverseStream(const int16_t* const src,
1490 const StreamConfig& input_config,
1491 const StreamConfig& output_config,
1492 int16_t* const dest) {
1493 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "AudioProcessing::ProcessReverseStream_AudioFrame");
1494
1495 if (input_config.num_channels() <= 0) {
1496 return AudioProcessing::Error::kBadNumberChannelsError;
1497 }
1498
1499 MutexLock lock(&mutex_render_);
1500 ProcessingConfig processing_config = formats_.api_format;
1501 processing_config.reverse_input_stream().set_sample_rate_hz(
1502 input_config.sample_rate_hz());
1503 processing_config.reverse_input_stream().set_num_channels(
1504 input_config.num_channels());
1505 processing_config.reverse_output_stream().set_sample_rate_hz(
1506 output_config.sample_rate_hz());
1507 processing_config.reverse_output_stream().set_num_channels(
1508 output_config.num_channels());
1509
1510 RETURN_ON_ERR(MaybeInitializeRender(processing_config));
1511 if (input_config.num_frames() !=
1512 formats_.api_format.reverse_input_stream().num_frames()) {
1513 return kBadDataLengthError;
1514 }
1515
1516 if (aec_dump_) {
1517 aec_dump_->WriteRenderStreamMessage(src, input_config.num_frames(),
1518 input_config.num_channels());
1519 }
1520
1521 render_.render_audio->CopyFrom(src, input_config);
1522 RETURN_ON_ERR(ProcessRenderStreamLocked());
1523 if (submodule_states_.RenderMultiBandProcessingActive() ||
1524 submodule_states_.RenderFullBandProcessingActive()) {
1525 render_.render_audio->CopyTo(output_config, dest);
1526 }
1527 return kNoError;
1528}
1529
1530int AudioProcessingImpl::ProcessRenderStreamLocked() {
1531 AudioBuffer* render_buffer = render_.render_audio.get(); // For brevity.
1532
1533 HandleRenderRuntimeSettings();
1534
1535 if (submodules_.render_pre_processor) {
1536 submodules_.render_pre_processor->Process(render_buffer);
1537 }
1538
1539 QueueNonbandedRenderAudio(render_buffer);
1540
1541 if (submodule_states_.RenderMultiBandSubModulesActive() &&
1542 SampleRateSupportsMultiBand(
1543 formats_.render_processing_format.sample_rate_hz())) {
1544 render_buffer->SplitIntoFrequencyBands();
1545 }
1546
1547 if (submodule_states_.RenderMultiBandSubModulesActive()) {
1548 QueueBandedRenderAudio(render_buffer);
1549 }
1550
1551 // TODO(peah): Perform the queuing inside QueueRenderAudiuo().
1552 if (submodules_.echo_controller) {
1553 submodules_.echo_controller->AnalyzeRender(render_buffer);
1554 }
1555
1556 if (submodule_states_.RenderMultiBandProcessingActive() &&
1557 SampleRateSupportsMultiBand(
1558 formats_.render_processing_format.sample_rate_hz())) {
1559 render_buffer->MergeFrequencyBands();
1560 }
1561
1562 return kNoError;
1563}

1565int AudioProcessingImpl::set_stream_delay_ms(int delay) {
1566 MutexLock lock(&mutex_capture_);
1567 Error retval = kNoError;
1568 capture_.was_stream_delay_set = true;
1569
1570 if (delay < 0) {
1571 delay = 0;
1572 retval = kBadStreamParameterWarning;
1573 }
1574
1575 // TODO(ajm): the max is rather arbitrarily chosen; investigate.
1576 if (delay > 500) {
1577 delay = 500;
1578 retval = kBadStreamParameterWarning;
1579 }
1580
1581 capture_nonlocked_.stream_delay_ms = delay;
1582 return retval;
1583}

1585bool AudioProcessingImpl::GetLinearAecOutput(
1586 rtc::ArrayView<std::array<float, 160>> linear_output) const {
1587 MutexLock lock(&mutex_capture_);
1588 AudioBuffer* linear_aec_buffer = capture_.linear_aec_output.get();
1589
1590 RTC_DCHECK(linear_aec_buffer);
1591 if (linear_aec_buffer) {
1592 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(1, linear_aec_buffer->num_bands());
1593 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(linear_output.size(), linear_aec_buffer->num_channels());
1594
1595 for (size_t ch = 0; ch < linear_aec_buffer->num_channels(); ++ch) {
1596 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(linear_output[ch].size(), linear_aec_buffer->num_frames());
1597 rtc::ArrayView<const float> channel_view =
1598 rtc::ArrayView<const float>(linear_aec_buffer->channels_const()[ch],
1599 linear_aec_buffer->num_frames());
1600 FloatS16ToFloat(channel_view.data(), channel_view.size(),
1601 linear_output[ch].data());
1602 }
1603 return true;
1604 }
1605 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "No linear AEC output available";
1606 RTC_NOTREACHED();
1607 return false;
1608}

1620void AudioProcessingImpl::set_stream_analog_level(int level) {
1621 MutexLock lock_capture(&mutex_capture_);
1622
1623 if (config_.capture_level_adjustment.analog_mic_gain_emulation.enabled) {
1624 // If the analog mic gain is emulated internally, simply cache the level for
1625 // later reporting back as the recommended stream analog level to use.
1626 capture_.cached_stream_analog_level_ = level;
1627 return;
1628 }
1629
1630 if (submodules_.agc_manager) {
1631 submodules_.agc_manager->set_stream_analog_level(level);
1632 data_dumper_->DumpRaw("experimental_gain_control_set_stream_analog_level",
1633 1, &level);
1634 return;
1635 }
1636
1637 if (submodules_.gain_control) {
1638 int error = submodules_.gain_control->set_stream_analog_level(level);
1639 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(kNoError, error);
1640 return;
1641 }
1642
1643 // If no analog mic gain control functionality is in place, cache the level
1644 // for later reporting back as the recommended stream analog level to use.
1645 capture_.cached_stream_analog_level_ = level;
1646}

1694
1695void AudioProcessingImpl::AttachAecDump(std::unique_ptr<AecDump> aec_dump) {
1696 RTC_DCHECK(aec_dump);
1697 MutexLock lock_render(&mutex_render_);
1698 MutexLock lock_capture(&mutex_capture_);
1699
1700 // The previously attached AecDump will be destroyed with the
1701 // 'aec_dump' parameter, which is after locks are released.
1702 aec_dump_.swap(aec_dump);
1703 WriteAecDumpConfigMessage(true);
1704 aec_dump_->WriteInitMessage(formats_.api_format, rtc::TimeUTCMillis());
1705}
1706
1707void AudioProcessingImpl::DetachAecDump() {
1708 // The d-tor of a task-queue based AecDump blocks until all pending
1709 // tasks are done. This construction avoids blocking while holding
1710 // the render and capture locks.
1711 std::unique_ptr<AecDump> aec_dump = nullptr;
1712 {
1713 MutexLock lock_render(&mutex_render_);
1714 MutexLock lock_capture(&mutex_capture_);
1715 aec_dump = std::move(aec_dump_);
1716 }

1735void AudioProcessingImpl::InitializeTransientSuppressor() {
1736 if (config_.transient_suppression.enabled &&
1737 !constants_.transient_suppressor_forced_off) {
1738 // Attempt to create a transient suppressor, if one is not already created.
1739 if (!submodules_.transient_suppressor) {
1740 submodules_.transient_suppressor =
1741 CreateTransientSuppressor(submodule_creation_overrides_);
1742 }
1743 if (submodules_.transient_suppressor) {
1744 submodules_.transient_suppressor->Initialize(
1745 proc_fullband_sample_rate_hz(), capture_nonlocked_.split_rate,
1746 num_proc_channels());
1747 } else {
1748 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
1749 << "No transient suppressor created (probably disabled)";
1750 }
1751 } else {
1752 submodules_.transient_suppressor.reset();
1753 }
1754}

1756void AudioProcessingImpl::InitializeHighPassFilter(bool forced_reset) {
1757 bool high_pass_filter_needed_by_aec =
1758 config_.echo_canceller.enabled &&
1759 config_.echo_canceller.enforce_high_pass_filtering &&
1760 !config_.echo_canceller.mobile_mode;
1761 if (submodule_states_.HighPassFilteringRequired() ||
1762 high_pass_filter_needed_by_aec) {
1763 bool use_full_band = config_.high_pass_filter.apply_in_full_band &&
1764 !constants_.enforce_split_band_hpf;
1765 int rate = use_full_band ? proc_fullband_sample_rate_hz()
1766 : proc_split_sample_rate_hz();
1767 size_t num_channels =
1768 use_full_band ? num_output_channels() : num_proc_channels();
1769
1770 if (!submodules_.high_pass_filter ||
1771 rate != submodules_.high_pass_filter->sample_rate_hz() ||
1772 forced_reset ||
1773 num_channels != submodules_.high_pass_filter->num_channels()) {
1774 submodules_.high_pass_filter.reset(
1775 new HighPassFilter(rate, num_channels));
1776 }
1777 } else {
1778 submodules_.high_pass_filter.reset();
1779 }
1780}

1786 } else {
1787 submodules_.voice_detector.reset();

1790void AudioProcessingImpl::InitializeEchoController() {
1791 bool use_echo_controller =
1792 echo_control_factory_ ||
1793 (config_.echo_canceller.enabled && !config_.echo_canceller.mobile_mode);
1794
1795 if (use_echo_controller) {
1796 // Create and activate the echo controller.
1797 if (echo_control_factory_) {
1798 submodules_.echo_controller = echo_control_factory_->Create(
1799 proc_sample_rate_hz(), num_reverse_channels(), num_proc_channels());
1800 RTC_DCHECK(submodules_.echo_controller);
1801 } else {
1802 EchoCanceller3Config config =
1803 use_setup_specific_default_aec3_config_
1804 ? EchoCanceller3::CreateDefaultConfig(num_reverse_channels(),
1805 num_proc_channels())
1806 : EchoCanceller3Config();
1807 submodules_.echo_controller = std::make_unique<EchoCanceller3>(
1808 config, proc_sample_rate_hz(), num_reverse_channels(),
1809 num_proc_channels());
1810 }
1811
1812 // Setup the storage for returning the linear AEC output.
1813 if (config_.echo_canceller.export_linear_aec_output) {
1814 constexpr int kLinearOutputRateHz = 16000;
1815 capture_.linear_aec_output = std::make_unique<AudioBuffer>(
1816 kLinearOutputRateHz, num_proc_channels(), kLinearOutputRateHz,
1817 num_proc_channels(), kLinearOutputRateHz, num_proc_channels());
1818 } else {
1819 capture_.linear_aec_output.reset();
1820 }
1821
1822 capture_nonlocked_.echo_controller_enabled = true;
1823
1824 submodules_.echo_control_mobile.reset();
1825 aecm_render_signal_queue_.reset();
1826 return;
1827 }
1828
1829 submodules_.echo_controller.reset();
1830 capture_nonlocked_.echo_controller_enabled = false;
1831 capture_.linear_aec_output.reset();
1832
1833 if (!config_.echo_canceller.enabled) {
1834 submodules_.echo_control_mobile.reset();
1835 aecm_render_signal_queue_.reset();
1836 return;
1837 }
1838
1839 if (config_.echo_canceller.mobile_mode) {
1840 // Create and activate AECM.
1841 size_t max_element_size =
1842 std::max(static_cast<size_t>(1),
1843 kMaxAllowedValuesOfSamplesPerBand *
1844 EchoControlMobileImpl::NumCancellersRequired(
1845 num_output_channels(), num_reverse_channels()));
1846
1847 std::vector<int16_t> template_queue_element(max_element_size);
1848
1849 aecm_render_signal_queue_.reset(
1850 new SwapQueue<std::vector<int16_t>, RenderQueueItemVerifier<int16_t>>(
1851 kMaxNumFramesToBuffer, template_queue_element,
1852 RenderQueueItemVerifier<int16_t>(max_element_size)));
1853
1854 aecm_render_queue_buffer_.resize(max_element_size);
1855 aecm_capture_queue_buffer_.resize(max_element_size);
1856
1857 submodules_.echo_control_mobile.reset(new EchoControlMobileImpl());
1858
1859 submodules_.echo_control_mobile->Initialize(proc_split_sample_rate_hz(),
1860 num_reverse_channels(),
1861 num_output_channels());
1862 return;
1863 }
1864
1865 submodules_.echo_control_mobile.reset();
1866 aecm_render_signal_queue_.reset();
1867}
1868
1869void AudioProcessingImpl::InitializeGainController1() {
1870 if (!config_.gain_controller1.enabled) {
1871 submodules_.agc_manager.reset();
1872 submodules_.gain_control.reset();
1873 return;
1874 }
1875
1876 if (!submodules_.gain_control) {
1877 submodules_.gain_control.reset(new GainControlImpl());
1878 }
1879
1880 submodules_.gain_control->Initialize(num_proc_channels(),
1881 proc_sample_rate_hz());
1882
1883 if (!config_.gain_controller1.analog_gain_controller.enabled) {
1884 int error = submodules_.gain_control->set_mode(
1885 Agc1ConfigModeToInterfaceMode(config_.gain_controller1.mode));
1886 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(kNoError, error);
1887 error = submodules_.gain_control->set_target_level_dbfs(
1888 config_.gain_controller1.target_level_dbfs);
1889 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(kNoError, error);
1890 error = submodules_.gain_control->set_compression_gain_db(
1891 config_.gain_controller1.compression_gain_db);
1892 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(kNoError, error);
1893 error = submodules_.gain_control->enable_limiter(
1894 config_.gain_controller1.enable_limiter);
1895 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(kNoError, error);
1896 error = submodules_.gain_control->set_analog_level_limits(
1897 config_.gain_controller1.analog_level_minimum,
1898 config_.gain_controller1.analog_level_maximum);
1899 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(kNoError, error);
1900
1901 submodules_.agc_manager.reset();
1902 return;
1903 }
1904
1905 if (!submodules_.agc_manager.get() ||
1906 submodules_.agc_manager->num_channels() !=
1907 static_cast<int>(num_proc_channels()) ||
1908 submodules_.agc_manager->sample_rate_hz() !=
1909 capture_nonlocked_.split_rate) {
1910 int stream_analog_level = -1;
1911 const bool re_creation = !!submodules_.agc_manager;
1912 if (re_creation) {
1913 stream_analog_level = submodules_.agc_manager->stream_analog_level();
1914 }
1915 submodules_.agc_manager.reset(new AgcManagerDirect(
1916 num_proc_channels(),
1917 config_.gain_controller1.analog_gain_controller.startup_min_volume,
1918 config_.gain_controller1.analog_gain_controller.clipped_level_min,
1919 !config_.gain_controller1.analog_gain_controller
1920 .enable_digital_adaptive,
1921 capture_nonlocked_.split_rate));
1922 if (re_creation) {
1923 submodules_.agc_manager->set_stream_analog_level(stream_analog_level);
1924 }
1925 }
1926 submodules_.agc_manager->Initialize();
1927 submodules_.agc_manager->SetupDigitalGainControl(
1928 submodules_.gain_control.get());
1929 submodules_.agc_manager->HandleCaptureOutputUsedChange(
1930 capture_.capture_output_used);
1931}

1949void AudioProcessingImpl::InitializeNoiseSuppressor() {
1950 submodules_.noise_suppressor.reset();
1951
1952 if (config_.noise_suppression.enabled) {
1953 auto map_level =
1954 [](AudioProcessing::Config::NoiseSuppression::Level level) {
1955 using NoiseSuppresionConfig =
1956 AudioProcessing::Config::NoiseSuppression;
1957 switch (level) {
1958 case NoiseSuppresionConfig::kLow:
1959 return NsConfig::SuppressionLevel::k6dB;
1960 case NoiseSuppresionConfig::kModerate:
1961 return NsConfig::SuppressionLevel::k12dB;
1962 case NoiseSuppresionConfig::kHigh:
1963 return NsConfig::SuppressionLevel::k18dB;
1964 case NoiseSuppresionConfig::kVeryHigh:
1965 return NsConfig::SuppressionLevel::k21dB;
1966 }
1967 RTC_CHECK_NOTREACHED();
1968 };
1969
1970 NsConfig cfg;
1971 cfg.target_level = map_level(config_.noise_suppression.level);
1972 submodules_.noise_suppressor = std::make_unique<NoiseSuppressor>(
1973 cfg, proc_sample_rate_hz(), num_proc_channels());
1974 }
1975}

1977void AudioProcessingImpl::InitializeCaptureLevelsAdjuster() {
1978 if (config_.pre_amplifier.enabled ||
1979 config_.capture_level_adjustment.enabled) {
1980 // Use both the pre-amplifier and the capture level adjustment gains as
1981 // pre-gains.
1982 float pre_gain = 1.f;
1983 if (config_.pre_amplifier.enabled) {
1984 pre_gain *= config_.pre_amplifier.fixed_gain_factor;
1985 }
1986 if (config_.capture_level_adjustment.enabled) {
1987 pre_gain *= config_.capture_level_adjustment.pre_gain_factor;
1988 }
1989
1990 submodules_.capture_levels_adjuster =
1991 std::make_unique<CaptureLevelsAdjuster>(
1992 config_.capture_level_adjustment.analog_mic_gain_emulation.enabled,
1993 config_.capture_level_adjustment.analog_mic_gain_emulation
1994 .initial_level,
1995 pre_gain, config_.capture_level_adjustment.post_gain_factor);
1996 } else {
1997 submodules_.capture_levels_adjuster.reset();
1998 }
1999}

2030void AudioProcessingImpl::WriteAecDumpConfigMessage(bool forced) {
2031 if (!aec_dump_) {
2032 return;
2033 }
2034
2035 std::string experiments_description = "";
2036 // TODO(peah): Add semicolon-separated concatenations of experiment
2037 // descriptions for other submodules.
2038 if (config_.gain_controller1.analog_gain_controller.clipped_level_min !=
2039 kClippedLevelMin) {
2040 experiments_description += "AgcClippingLevelExperiment;";
2041 }
2042 if (!!submodules_.capture_post_processor) {
2043 experiments_description += "CapturePostProcessor;";
2044 }
2045 if (!!submodules_.render_pre_processor) {
2046 experiments_description += "RenderPreProcessor;";
2047 }
2048 if (capture_nonlocked_.echo_controller_enabled) {
2049 experiments_description += "EchoController;";
2050 }
2051 if (config_.gain_controller2.enabled) {
2052 experiments_description += "GainController2;";
2053 }
2054
2055 InternalAPMConfig apm_config;
2056
2057 apm_config.aec_enabled = config_.echo_canceller.enabled;
2058 apm_config.aec_delay_agnostic_enabled = false;
2059 apm_config.aec_extended_filter_enabled = false;
2060 apm_config.aec_suppression_level = 0;
2061
2062 apm_config.aecm_enabled = !!submodules_.echo_control_mobile;
2063 apm_config.aecm_comfort_noise_enabled =
2064 submodules_.echo_control_mobile &&
2065 submodules_.echo_control_mobile->is_comfort_noise_enabled();
2066 apm_config.aecm_routing_mode =
2067 submodules_.echo_control_mobile
2068 ? static_cast<int>(submodules_.echo_control_mobile->routing_mode())
2069 : 0;
2070
2071 apm_config.agc_enabled = !!submodules_.gain_control;
2072
2073 apm_config.agc_mode = submodules_.gain_control
2074 ? static_cast<int>(submodules_.gain_control->mode())
2075 : GainControl::kAdaptiveAnalog;
2076 apm_config.agc_limiter_enabled =
2077 submodules_.gain_control ? submodules_.gain_control->is_limiter_enabled()
2078 : false;
2079 apm_config.noise_robust_agc_enabled = !!submodules_.agc_manager;
2080
2081 apm_config.hpf_enabled = config_.high_pass_filter.enabled;
2082
2083 apm_config.ns_enabled = config_.noise_suppression.enabled;
2084 apm_config.ns_level = static_cast<int>(config_.noise_suppression.level);
2085
2086 apm_config.transient_suppression_enabled =
2087 config_.transient_suppression.enabled;
2088 apm_config.experiments_description = experiments_description;
2089 apm_config.pre_amplifier_enabled = config_.pre_amplifier.enabled;
2090 apm_config.pre_amplifier_fixed_gain_factor =
2091 config_.pre_amplifier.fixed_gain_factor;
2092
2093 if (!forced && apm_config == apm_config_for_aec_dump_) {
2094 return;
2095 }
2096 aec_dump_->WriteConfig(apm_config);
2097 apm_config_for_aec_dump_ = apm_config;
2098}
